      "content": "thanks, this is really helpful for them. i've noticed that whenever my students try to bring up these specific points—like the strain on local resources or the constitutional authority of the federal government—their opponents often dismiss them as \"anti-immigrant rhetoric\" or claim they are ignoring the obvious economic benefits of migrant labor. how should my students respond to those specific rebuttals to show that their position is based on legal and fiscal principles rather than just being \"anti-immigrant\"?",
